data.title: S4 Capital launches white paper on AI Search Era's impact on marketers, Oct 30, 2025. Monks leads the charge.
data.description: In New York on October 30, 2025, it was reported that the increasing prominence of AI-powered search technology is causing companies to reassess their strategies for maintaining visibility in a world that is becoming more dependent on machines. As a response to this significant change, Monks, a digital brand operating worldwide under S4Capital plc, which relies solely on data-driven techniques, is taking proactive measures.

data.title: Western Digital stock surges post-Q1 earnings: Revenue $2.82B, EPS $1.78 (est. $1.58), total revenue up 27%.
data.description: Western Digital Corp (NASDAQ: WDC) stock is surging in after-hours trading following the release of its fiscal first-quarter results. Key highlights include Q1 revenue reaching $2.82 billion, exceeding estimates of $2.73 billion, and Q1 adjusted EPS coming in at $1.78, higher than the anticipated $1.58. Total revenue witnessed a 27% increase compared to the previous year. Cash flow from operations amounted to $672 million, with free cash flow reported at $599 million for the quarter. For more detailed information, the full story can be accessed on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Rocket Companies Inc. (NYSE: RKT) beats Q3 earnings with revenue of $1.78 billion and earnings of seven cents per share. Stock climbs.
data.description: Rocket Companies Inc. saw its shares on NYSE (RKT) rise as it surpassed expectations with its third-quarter earnings report. The company reported earnings of seven cents per share, beating the expected five cents. Quarterly revenue exceeded estimates, coming in at $1.78 billion compared to the anticipated $1.66 billion. These positive figures led to an increase in RKT stock. For a more detailed analysis, visit the full story on a financial news website.

data.title: High demand for ‘KPop Demon Hunters’ costume this Halloween as scarcity leads to improvisation for fans.
data.description: Costumes from a popular Netflix movie have become highly sought after this year, with limited availability causing individuals to get creative in replicating the looks.

data.title: Investors unimpressed by Trump-Xi meeting covering tariffs and trade barriers; uncertainty lingers on reaching a permanent agreement.
data.description: The much-anticipated event extensively discussed tariff and trade barriers, addressing numerous aspects of the issue. However, uncertainties persist regarding the achievement of a lasting agreement.

data.title: China suspends recent export controls on rare earths; remains silent on previous rules causing global disruption.
data.description: Export controls recently announced by China have been halted, however, there has been no mention of the regulations put in place earlier. These rules, which have caused disruptions in global supply chains, remain in place. This move comes amidst a surge in demand for goods and materials, with the export controls impacting various industries. China's decision has brought relief to many businesses, but concerns linger about the ongoing impact of the previously implemented restrictions. The pause in export controls is significant for both domestic and international markets, as uncertainty continues to surround China's trade policies.

data.title: Trump and Xi reach 1-year truce to ease trade war, China suspends rare earth export limits, US cuts fentanyl tariffs by half.
data.description: In a recent development, China has decided to temporarily lift restrictions on the export of rare earth metals for a period of one year. This decision comes as the U.S. has reciprocated by reducing its tariffs on fentanyl imports by half. The move marks a step towards easing trade tensions between the two countries.

data.title: Shutdown worsens economy's uncertainty: Tariffs, loss of data. How will the missing figures affect the economic outlook?
data.description: The economy was already facing challenges due to tariffs and uncertainty, with key economic indicators becoming increasingly difficult to interpret. However, the recent government shutdown has exacerbated the situation by resulting in a loss of crucial data that is vital for understanding the state of the economy. This lack of information has further complicated the economic analysis and decision-making processes, adding to the existing challenges.

data.title: Some candy companies reducing cocoa to save money due to rising prices amidst climate change impact.
data.description: Due to the impact of climate change, cocoa prices have surged, leading companies to make slight adjustments to candy recipes.

data.title: Starbucks sees slight sales growth, but net income drops by 85% due to charges for store closures and layoffs.
data.description: The company's net income dropped by 85 percent due to expenses linked to shutting down stores and cutting corporate jobs.

data.title: Trump considers selling Nvidia's Blackwell chips to China, sparking national security concerns. Summit on Thursday to discuss.
data.description: The sale of Nvidia's Blackwell chips will be a topic of discussion at an upcoming summit on Thursday, as confirmed by the president. U.S. officials caution that such a sale could have significant national security implications, describing it as a potentially "massive" mistake.

data.title: Microsoft boosts investments in A.I. with $34.9 billion capital expenditures in latest quarter.
data.description: In its most recent quarter, the company disclosed capital expenditures totaling $34.9 billion, which exceeded initial projections.

data.title: FDA aims to expedite approvals for cheaper copycat drugs similar to generics, potentially reducing drug costs.
data.description: The agency revealed plans to reduce regulatory barriers for manufacturers of biosimilar medications, which are similar to generics and hold the potential to decrease drug expenses. The initiative aims to streamline the approval process for biosimilars, boosting competition and potentially driving down prices. This move is expected to benefit both patients and healthcare systems, as it could lead to significant cost savings in the pharmaceutical sector.

data.title: 'Ethereum devs announce final date for Fusaka upgrade introducing PeerDAS in early December, a big move for the platform.'
data.description: In early December, Fusaka is set to launch a new data-sampling method for transactions known as PeerDAS. This innovative system aims to enhance efficiency in data processing for transactions. Stay tuned for the upcoming debut of Fusaka and its groundbreaking technology.

data.title: Global Revenue Cycle Management market to grow at 45.95% CAGR, exceeding USD 28560 billion by 2035 from USD 449.83 billion in 2024.
data.description: In New York as of October 30, 2025, it has been reported that the projected Global Revenue Cycle Management (RCM) Market is set to experience significant growth. Starting at USD 449.83 billion in 2024, the market is anticipated to reach a value of USD 28560 billion by 2035. This represents a remarkable Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of 45.95% throughout the forecast period. This substantial increase in value highlights the substantial potential for development in this industry.

data.title: Beneficient is back in compliance with Nasdaq's periodic filing and market value requirements.
data.description: Beneficient has successfully met Nasdaq's filing requirement and demonstrated a compliance with the market value of listed securities. This development signifies the company's adherence to Nasdaq regulations. The achievement is significant for Beneficient as it ensures continued listing on the exchange, safeguarding investor confidence. This compliance reflects positively on the company's financial health and stability. The successful compliance encompasses meeting specific criteria related to financial filings and market value of securities, which are crucial for maintaining a presence on Nasdaq.

data.title: Atypical Teratoid/Rhabdoid Tumor market sees promising growth with CAGR during 2025-2034, driven by rising molecular diagnosis & new therapies. Expanding pool of identified patients due to increased awareness.
data.description: The market for atypical teratoid/rhabdoid tumor is experiencing growth due to a surge in molecular diagnosis and higher awareness of this aggressive pediatric CNS cancer. This has led to an increase in the number of identified patients. Furthermore, the introduction of new therapies like PD-1 inhibitor is contributing to the market expansion.

data.title: Mayfair Gold Corp. to participate in the 51st Annual New Orleans Investment Conference on November. TSXV: MFG, OTCQX: MFGCF.
data.description: Mayfair Gold Corp., a Vancouver-based company listed on the TSXV as MFG and OTCQX as MFGCF, has confirmed its participation in the upcoming 51st Annual New Orleans Investment Conference at the Hilton New Orleans Riverside in November 2025.
